<html>
	<head>
	<style type="text/css">
		body {
			background-color : #efefef;
			font-family : Arial, Tahoma, Verdana;
			font-size : 8pt;
		}
		h1 {
			font-size : 12pt;
			color : #006699;
		}
		.code {
			background-color : #ffffff;
			width: 100%;
			font-family : "Courier New";
			border: 1px #c0c0c0 solid;
			padding: 2px;
			font-size : 10pt;
		}
	</style>
	</head>
	<body>
	<h1>NSP Example</h1>
	This page is an example of how you can host script pages similar to PHP, ASP, JSP, BSP, etc.<br/><br/>
	<b>The current system date is: <%=new Date()%></b><br/><br/>
	The code is found below:
	<div class="code"><%
	// Example Script snippet, let's read our own source since we want to show it.
	fs = require("fs");
	var data = fs.readFileSync("webroot/test.nsp");
	var source = data.toString();
	// Regurgitate it as source not HTML
	source = source.replace(/</g, "&lt;").replace(/>/g, "&gt;").replace(/\n/g, "<br/>");
	context.write(source);
	%></div>
	</body>
</html>